-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Method 1: Startup Folder

Press Win + R, type shell:startup, and press Enter.

This opens the Startup folder.

Copy a shortcut of your app into this folder.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Windows (Task Scheduler)

Press Win + R, type taskschd.msc, press Enter.

In Task Scheduler, click Create Basic Task.

Name it (e.g., "Open My App").

Choose Daily.

Set the time to 4:50 PM.

Under Action, choose Start a program.

Browse to your app’s .exe file.

Finish → Done.

